'I don't know what the future holds for us,' the 44-year-old told the Spanish media on Wednesday. 'We all think that Messi will be at Barca in the next few years and that is what all the cules (Barca fans) want.

'The thought of having a team without Messi is not even something we contemplate.'

Messi, who is Barca's all-time top scorer in all official club competitions, is under contract with the Catalan giants until June 2018.

He has been instrumental in helping Barca win 21 trophies, including six La Liga titles and three Champions League.

