'This is what we are looking for, even though we know that things on the outside can change within five seconds.'

The Catalan club began 2015 with a 1-0 defeat to Real Sociedad and the following day sacked sporting director Andoni Zubizarreta, with former captain Carles Puyol leaving his role as Zubizarreta's assistant hours later.

When asked about reports in the local media that former player Jose Mari Bakero was the leading candidate to replace Zubizarreta, Enrique said: 'This is a question for our president (Josep Maria Bartomeu). All I can say is that I have a good opinion of him.'

 

